Decide your target domain. Replace all example.com below with your actual target.

text
$domain = "example.com"
Subdomain Enumeration

text
subfinder.exe -d $domain -o subfinder.txt
amass.exe enum -passive -d $domain -o amass.txt
Subdomain Permutation/Expansion

text
alterx.exe -l subfinder.txt -o alterx1.txt
alterx.exe -l amass.txt -o alterx2.txt
Combine and Deduplicate All Subdomains

text
Get-Content subfinder.txt, amass.txt, alterx1.txt, alterx2.txt | Sort-Object -Unique | Set-Content all_subdomains.txt
DNS Resolution

text
dnsx.exe -l all_subdomains.txt -o resolved.txt
Probe for Live HTTP Hosts

text
httpx.exe -l resolved.txt -silent -o alive.txt
URL and Endpoint Collection

text
gau.exe -o gau.txt < alive.txt
waybackurls.exe -input alive.txt -output wayback.txt
hakrawler.exe -url-file alive.txt -depth 2 -plain -out hakrawler.txt
katana.exe -list alive.txt -o katana.txt
To combine and deduplicate collected URLs:

text
Get-Content gau.txt, wayback.txt, hakrawler.txt, katana.txt | Sort-Object -Unique | Set-Content all_urls.txt
Extract Relevant Parameters (GF Patterns)

text
gf.exe xss all_urls.txt > xss_candidates.txt
gf.exe sqli all_urls.txt > sqli_candidates.txt
gf.exe idor all_urls.txt > idor_candidates.txt
Parameter XSS Testing

text
dalfox.exe file xss_candidates.txt -o dalfox_xss.txt
Active Fuzzing (optional)

text
ffuf.exe -u https://$domain/FUZZ -w wordlist.txt -o ffuf_result.json
Automated Vulnerability Scanning

text
nuclei.exe -ut
nuclei.exe -l alive.txt -severity critical,high,medium -es info -o nuclei_critical.txt
Reporting

Review result files:

all_subdomains.txt (unique subdomains)

resolved.txt (actual DNS records)

alive.txt (live HTTP hosts)

all_urls.txt (unique gathered URLs)

nuclei_critical.txt (vuln scan summary)

dalfox_xss.txt (XSS findings)

Fuzz JSON and GF parameter files
